snippet.textDisplay:
Kat isn't the nicest person that everyone is making her out to be. She was abusive and quite rude to quite a few of my friends. Not to mention they had first hand experience of interacting with her, even in person. They were in some of Kat's tiktoks for a while. They were also a mod for one of her discords for a while and actually experienced what it was like to be her friend. One of these friends was extremely suicidal, but every time they went to Kat for comfort, because that's what you would expect as a best friend. Unfortunately, Kat was also the kind of person to never be there for someone when they needed it.
There are also screenshots of a conversation between Kat talking shit about this friend and joking about hiring a hitman for this friend because they didn't want to deal with them anymore and ridding themselves of a problem forever.
It's okay to be famous, but be humble. It's not okay to let the fame go to your head and treat your friends/fans like shit.
Thanks for coming to my Ted talk.
